Author: DoubleGate <parobek@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 31 23:17:34 2026 -0400

    feat(v2.0): Phase 3 — Sprites On Scanline 0 (pre-render line-5 sprite fetch)
    
    First increment of the PPU sprite-shifter "bleeding-edge" cluster, behind a
    new default-OFF feature `ppu-sprite-shifter-counter` (forwarded nes-ppu ->
    nes-core -> nes-test-harness). Default build byte-identical.
    
    AccuracyCoin "Sprites On Scanline 0" asserts that OAM data CAN draw on
    scanline 0: the pre-render line is treated as scanline (prerender_line & 0xFF)
    = 5 (NTSC 261 & 255) for the sprite-tile in-range check during dots 257-320, so
    a sprite whose pixel lands on row 5 loads into the shifters for scanline 0 (the
    data comes from STALE secondary OAM when rendering was disabled during the
    eval). RustyNES used -1 as the pre-render y-test reference ("scanline 0 never
    displays sprites"), which the test disproves.
    
    `fetch_sprite_tile` (feature on): next_line for the pre-render line = 5 instead
    of -1, plus an in-range gate on the shifter load (only load slots whose row =
    next_line - y is in [0, height)). On visible scanlines the gate is a no-op (the
    eval's identical row test already guarantees every in_use slot is in-range, so
    load == in_use); only the pre-render line's stale secondary-OAM slots are
    filtered. The eval reference (tick_sprite_eval_per_dot) keeps -1 so a Y=0
    sprite with rendering on does NOT appear on scanline 0 (test 1's false-positive
    check).
    
    Validation (feature on): "Sprites On Scanline 0" Fail -> PASS; AccuracyCoin
    (r4) 28 -> 27 fail; cpu_interrupts_v2 5/5; ppu_vbl_nmi 10/10; nes-ppu 41/41;
    Sprite 0 Hit + overflow still pass; clippy clean (default + feature). Default
    build (feature off) byte-identical. The other 3 cluster tests (Stale BG/Sprite
    Shift, BG Serial In) remain — they need the shifter rendering-gate + serial-in
    modeling (next increments).
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

